We could have stayed at a much nicer hotel for the price, but since it was non-refundable, we continued to stay there.	We would deffinately stay here again, everyone was very nice and the location was worth it for what we got in our room just for being a little outside of Times Square.	I would definately recommend the Murray Hill East and wouldn't hesitate to stay there in the future.	We stayed at this hotel on a business trip, because there weren't a lot of other hotels available in the company's price range.	We have stayed elsewhere, but nowhere else is as good and we will always stay here is there are rooms available.